get%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EArtificial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20transforming%20corporate%20America%2C%20yet%20the%20boom%20remains%20understated%20in%20government%20growth%20statistics%2C%20according%20to%20Goldman%20Sachs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20at%20Goldman%20pointed%20to%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20boom%20in%20a%20Saturday%20note%3A%20%26quot%3BRevenue%20at%20US%20companies%20providing%20AI%20infrastructure%20has%20risen%20by%20%24400bn%20since%202022%2C%20which%20at%20first%20glance%20seems%20to%20suggest%20that%20AI%20has%20been%20a%20meaningful%20driver%20of%20economic%20growth%20recently.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20official%20numbers%20tell%20a%20different%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20technology%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20lifted%20real%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feconomy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUS%20economic%20activity%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20about%20%24160%20billion%20since%202022%2C%20or%200.7%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20the%20analysts%20calculated.%20Yet%20only%20around%20%2445%20billion%2C%20or%200.2%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20of%20AI-spurred%20growth%20has%20been%20recorded%20in%20official%20statistics.%20That%20leaves%20roughly%20%24115%20billion%20uncounted%2C%20according%20to%20the%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20gap%20highlights%20the%20difference%20between%20what%20companies%20report%20and%20what%20the%20government%20measures%20due%20to%20the%20Commerce%20Department's%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20method%20for%20calculating%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20measured%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20GDP%20is%20likely%20much%20smaller%20because%20the%20BEA's%20methodology%20for%20estimating%20GDP%20treats%20semiconductors%20as%20intermediate%20inputs%2C%20which%20are%20only%20counted%20towards%20final%20demand%20when%20the%20products%20(e.g.%2C%20consumer%20laptops)%20that%20they%20enable%20are%20sold%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20the%20Goldman%20analysts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20high-performance%20semiconductors%20%E2%80%94%20the%20chips%20powering%20AI%20training%20%E2%80%94%20are%20classified%20as%20intermediate%20inputs.%20When%20they're%20imported%2C%20the%20value%20is%20deducted%20from%20GDP%2C%20and%20their%20use%20in%20building%20AI%20systems%20doesn't%20appear%20as%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20chips%20developed%20in%20recent%20years%20are%20being%20used%20for%20training%20and%20supporting%20AI%20models%20%E2%80%94%20essentially%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20an%20intangible%20asset%20of%20which%20the%20ultimate%20output%20value%20has%20not%20been%20fully%20capitalized%20or%20measured%20in%20GDP%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman's%20analysts%20estimated%20that%20around%20%2475%20billion%20spent%20on%20developing%20AI%20models%20and%20enterprise%20solutions%20in%20the%20cloud%20has%20not%20been%20counted%20in%20investment%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENew%20import%20policies%20complicated%20the%20picture%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20half%20of%202025%2C%20business%20investment%20in%20information-processing%20equipment%20appeared%20to%20jump%2C%20largely%20because%20companies%20rushed%20to%20import%20servers%20and%20networking%20gear%20ahead%20of%20President%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftrump-tariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDonald%20Trump's%20import%20tariffs.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20%26quot%3Bprobably%20reflects%20one-time%20frontloading%20ahead%20of%20tariffs%20and%20thus%20exaggerates%20normal%20AI%20investment%20demand%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20analysts%20wrote.%20Because%20imports%20are%20subtracted%20from%20GDP%2C%20the%20investment%20boost%20was%20partly%20offset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI's%20impact%20is%20hard%20to%20pin%20down%20in%20other%20important%20indicators.%20Companies%2C%20too%2C%20are%20struggling%20to%20show%20it%20in%20their%20bottom%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp