roduct%20and%20engineering%20for%20OpenAI's%20developer%20platform%2C%20respectively.%20During%20an%20interview%20on%20the%20BG2%20podcast%20that%20aired%20Thursday%2C%20Godement%20and%20Wu%20shared%20three%20tips%20on%20how%20companies%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-in-action-company-workforce-strategies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eintegrate%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNumber%20one%20is%20the%20interesting%20combination%20of%20top-down%20buy-in%20and%20enabling%20a%20very%20clear%20group%2C%20like%20a%20tiger%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20Godement%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20the%20team%20could%20be%20a%20mix%20of%20staff%20from%20AI%20providers%20like%20OpenAI%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20company's%20own%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGodement%20said%20members%20of%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcisco-tiger-team-attack-arista-networks-2017-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etiger%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20should%20possess%20either%20technical%20skills%20or%20a%20deep%20understanding%20of%20the%20company's%20processes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20enterprise%2C%20like%20customer%20support%2C%20what%20we%20found%20is%20that%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20knowledge%20is%20in%20people's%20heads%2C%26quot%3B%20Godement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnless%20you%20have%20that%20tiger%20team%2C%20a%20mix%20of%20technical%20and%20subject%20matter%20experts%2C%20it's%20really%20hard%20to%20get%20something%20out%20of%20the%20ground%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20Godement%20and%20Wu%20said%20companies%20need%20to%20develop%20clear%20benchmarks%2C%20or%20what%20they%20call%20%26quot%3Bevals%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20track%20their%20progress%20with%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvals%20are%20much%20harder%20than%20what%20it%20looks%20to%20get%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Godement%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvals%2C%20oftentimes%2C%20need%20to%20come%20bottom-up%2C%20because%20all%20of%20these%20things%20are%20kind%20of%20in%20people's%20heads%2C%20in%20the%20actual%20operator's%20heads.%20It's%20actually%20very%20hard%20to%20have%20a%20top-down%20mandate%2C%26quot%3B%20Wu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20Godement%20said%20that%20companies%20should%20monitor%20their%20benchmarks%20closely%20and%20strive%20to%20make%20progress%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20that%20is%20like%20art%20sometimes%2C%20more%20than%20science%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProgress%20can%20be%20achieved%20by%20having%20a%20good%20understanding%20of%20an%20AI%20model's%20design%2C%20behavior%2C%20and%20constraints%2C%20Godement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20we%20even%20need%20to%20fine-tune%20ourselves%20the%20models%2C%20when%20there%20are%20some%20clear%20limitations%2C%20and%20you%20know%2C%20being%20patient%2C%20getting%20you%20way%20up%20there%20and%20then%2C%20ship%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGodement%20said%20it%20was%20important%20for%20a%20company's%20top%20leadership%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-top-priority-ceos-going-into-next-year-mckinsey-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emake%20AI%20a%20priority%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20give%20their%20staff%20the%20opportunity%20to%20experiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLetting%20the%20team%20organize%20and%20be%20like%2C%20'OK%2C%20if%20you%20want%20to%20start%20small%2C%20start%20small%2C%20and%20then%20you%20can%20scale%20it%20up.'%20That%20would%20be%20number%201%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20CEOs%20have%20been%20stepping%20up%20their%20efforts%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20getting%20their%20employees%20to%20use%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuolingo%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fduolingo-ceo-does-not-plan-lay-o