3EIt%20was%20scary%20to%20give%20up%20the%20health%20benefits%20and%20a%20steady%20paycheck%2C%20but%20what%20once%20felt%20like%20a%20dream%20role%20had%20left%20me%20burned%20out%20and%20deeply%20unhappy.%20So%2C%20I%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20we%20set%20our%20sights%20on%20Mexico%20as%20it's%20where%20my%20grandparents%20were%20born%2C%20and%20I'd%20always%20felt%20a%20pull%20to%20connect%20with%20my%20roots%20and%20learn%20Spanish.%20It%20also%20didn't%20hurt%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20there%20seemed%20lower%20than%20in%20many%20other%20places%20we%20researched.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20planned%20to%20spend%20just%20over%20six%20weeks%20in%20Mexico%20before%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-moved-to-italy-for-work-now-back-in-us-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereturning%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trip%20would%20be%20a%20trial%20run%20of%20sorts%20to%20see%20if%20we%20could%20handle%20living%20abroad%20and%2C%20more%20importantly%2C%20if%20we%20liked%20this%20lifestyle%20enough%20to%20make%20it%20permanent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20figuring%20out%20the%20paperwork%20we%20needed%20to%20fly%20our%20cat%20to%20Mexico%20and%20putting%20most%20of%20our%20belongings%20in%20storage%2C%20we%20gave%20up%20our%20Brooklyn%20apartment%20and%20took%20the%20leap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20first%20stop%20was%20Puerto%20Escondido%20in%20Oaxaca%2C%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fwhere-to-travel-around-the-world-2021%2Fthings-to-do-in-mexico-city%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMexico%20City%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228dba4c42-0cd7-439d-aac4-0c45a9859343%5C%22%3EOur%20time%20in%20Mexico%20felt%20like%20a%20reset%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENestled%20along%20the%20Pacific%2C%20Puerto%20Escondido%20was%20magic%20with%20its%20turquoise%20waters%20and%20warm%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELocals%20and%20expats%20seemed%20to%20blend%20together%20seamlessly%2C%20and%20the%20pace%20of%20life%20invited%20me%20to%20slow%20down.%20The%20lower%20cost%20of%20living%20was%20a%20welcome%20change%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20local%20market%2C%20I%20could%20get%20a%20week's%20worth%20of%20groceries%20for%20about%20%2435%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fraction%20of%20what%20we'd%20been%20spending%20before.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20better%2C%20dining%20out%20didn't%20break%20the%20bank.%20We%20were%20able%20to%20eat%20at%20some%20amazing%20restaurants%20for%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20what%20we%20would've%20spent%20in%20NYC%20for%20similar%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hand%20holding%20coffee%20cup%20over%20blue-green%20pool%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68b09b14cfc04e97619c3a4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhile%20in%20Mexico%2C%20I%20felt%20my%20creative%20spark%20coming%20back%20to%20me.%3Cp%3ESandra%20Salathe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%2C%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-city-to-small-coastal-village-better-than-suburb-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etiny%20coastal%20town%3C%2Fa%3E%20began%20to%20heal%20me%20in%20ways%20I%20didn't%20know%20I%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20heartbreaking%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquitting-after-less-than-year-ok-leave-good-terms-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleave%20a%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20I'd%20once%20dreamed%20of%20and%20to%20realize%20it%20was%20slowly%20breaking%20me%20apart.%20But%20in%20Puerto%2C%20I%20felt%20my%20creative%20spark%20return.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20my%20savings%20and%20a%20fianc%C3%A9%20whose%20income%20covered%20us%20both%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20take%20time%20off%20without%20the%20immediate%20pressure%20of%20figuring%20out%20my%20next%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20my%20days%20at%208%20a.m.%2C%20with%20no%20office%20to%20rush%20to.%20I'd%20swim%20in%20the%20Airbnb's%20pool%2C%20make%20breakfast%2C%20do%20freelance%20work%20at%20a%20nearby%20coworking%20space%20until%203%20p.m.%2C%20and%20then%20hit%20the%20beach%20to%20watch%20the%20sunset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22780225c0-4cc0-48b4-b3d0-77d12013272f%5C%22%3EThough%20our%20travels%20weren't%20always%20smooth%20sailing%2C%20they've%20only%20made%20us%20stronger%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20weeks%20in%20Puerto%2C%20we%20packed%20up%20and%20headed%20to%20Mexico%20City.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20arrived%2C%20my%20fianc%C3%A9%20had%20a%20health%20scare.%20I%20found%20an%20urgent-care%20clinic%20nearby%2C%20and%20our%20limited%20Spanish%20and%20the%20staff's%20patience%20got%20us%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20seen%20quickly%2C%20and%20the%20visit%20cost%20about%20%24250%20after%20conversion%20rates%2C%20without%20insurance.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20we'd%20probably%20have%20paid%2010%20times%20as%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThankfully%2C%20my%20fianc%C3%A9%20quickly%20recovered%2C%20and%20making%20it%20through%20this%20experience%20felt%20like%20more%20proof%20that%20we%20could%20tackle%20whatever%20obstacles%20life%20abroad%20may%20bring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20wasn't%20the%20only%20difficult%20part%20of%20our%20travels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20excited%20as%20I%20was%20to%20bounce%20around%2C%20I%20didn't%20fully%20grasp%20how%20isolating%20it%20can%20feel%20to%20not%20have%20a%20permanent%20home%20base%20and%20be%20far%20from%20our%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20loneliness%20started%20to%20seep%20into%20my%20relationship%20with%20my%20fianc%C3%A9.%20No%20matter%20how%20solid%20and%20healthy%20we%20are%2C%20he%20became%20my%20only%20support%20system%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that's%20a%20lot%20to%20place%20on%20one%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20stressed%2C%20he%20bore%20the%20brunt%20of%20it%2C%20and%20vice%20versa.%20Back%20in%20New%20York%2C%20we%20each%20had%20close%20fr